:INFO
ADHD Task Management Tools
A comparison of tools suited to ADHD brains. The best tool is the one you actually open. Prioritize low friction over feature richness.

:TASK
[ ] Todoist: strong capture, good mobile app, can become overwhelming
[ ] Things 3 (Apple only): clean design, area-based organization, offline
[ ] Notion: flexible but high setup cost, easy to over-engineer
[ ] Paper index cards: zero friction, no syncing, best for do-now lists
[ ] Amplenote: combines notes and tasks, jot score helps prioritization
[ ] TickTick: includes Pomodoro timer, good calendar integration

:NOTE
Avoid switching tools more than once per year. The novelty of a new app mimics productivity without producing it. Commit to one system for 90 days before evaluating.

:LINK
https://www.amplenote.com
Amplenote: notes plus task management with priority scoring
